# {{.Feature}}/stores/turso

The {{.Feature}} feature's Turso/libSQL store adapter — its own module, so a host
that brings a different datastore never pulls libsql into its graph.

- `Repositories(db)` returns a `{{.Feature}}.Repositories` after probing the
  `{{.Agg}}` table (boot-time; errors if the `{{.Source}}` migration source was
  not applied).
- `ExportMigrations(dst)` copies the canonical SQL into a host's migration dir
  (scaffold-and-own — the host applies it pre-boot).
- `MigrationsFS` / `MigrationsDir` expose the embedded schema for a host runner.

Conformance (`storetest.Run`) is env-gated behind `-tags=integration`:

```
TURSO_DATABASE_URL=... TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=... go test -tags=integration ./...
```

Without the env it skips loudly. `TestExportMigrations` runs hermetically on
plain `go test ./...`.
